WEBVTT

00:06.173 --> 00:09.176
<i>[pensive instrumental music]</i>

00:09.176 --> 00:16.183
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:23.065 --> 00:26.110
<i>[woman singing in Norwegian]</i>

00:26.110 --> 00:33.117
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:45.796 --> 00:52.803
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:13.157 --> 01:16.160
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

01:16.160 --> 01:23.167
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:53.531 --> 01:59.995
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:10.840 --> 02:13.133
<i>Earther attacking
ship</i> milowda.

02:13.133 --> 02:15.135
We na du nating nada.

02:15.135 --> 02:17.805
<i>[overlapping shouting]</i>

02:17.805 --> 02:19.723
It's been running on
every news feed in the Belt.

02:19.723 --> 02:22.977
<i>[overlapping shouting]</i>

02:22.977 --> 02:25.813
<i>They</i> gonya <i>kill all</i> milowda.

02:25.813 --> 02:28.607
<i>[explosions]</i>

02:29.441 --> 02:32.820
<i>This was an unprovoked attack
by the UN.</i>

02:32.820 --> 02:35.489
<i>These actions
endanger the armistice</i>

02:35.489 --> 02:38.868
<i>and put the alliance around
the Ring Gate in jeopardy.</i>

02:38.868 --> 02:41.078
<i>[man] Secretary-General
candidate Nancy Gao</i>

02:41.078 --> 02:43.539
<i>has called
for an investigation.</i>

02:43.539 --> 02:45.249
<i>This truly is a tragedy
on all sides.</i>

02:45.249 --> 02:47.751
<i>The OPA is our ally.</i>

02:47.751 --> 02:50.546
<i>Peace between our nations
is essential</i>

02:50.546 --> 02:52.423
<i>for the colonization
of the new worlds.</i>

02:52.423 --> 02:53.841
[monitor blips]

02:53.841 --> 02:55.634
Gao is going
to push this hard.

02:55.634 --> 02:57.469
We need to change
the narrative.

02:57.469 --> 02:59.513
I think that you should
get on the road,

02:59.513 --> 03:01.307
speak directly
to the voters...

03:02.099 --> 03:04.727
Ma'am, General McCourt
is here to see you.

03:05.436 --> 03:06.270
Send him in.

03:07.396 --> 03:08.772
Close the door on your way out.

03:14.278 --> 03:16.488
- Good morning, ma'am.
- Good morning, General.

03:16.488 --> 03:18.240
I know this has been
a rough day for you.

03:18.240 --> 03:21.327
Yes, ma'am, one of the most
difficult days of my career.

03:21.327 --> 03:24.496
- For me as well.
- Madam Secretary.

03:28.125 --> 03:29.710
I'm here to tender
my resignation.

03:29.710 --> 03:33.339
General, you do not need
to fall on your sword over this.

03:33.339 --> 03:35.007
I understand that's how
the public will perceive it,

03:35.007 --> 03:36.800
but that's not what I'm doing.

03:36.800 --> 03:38.802
I'm a marine.
You're the commander in chief.

03:38.802 --> 03:40.763
I've always followed
your orders to the letter,

03:40.763 --> 03:43.265
but I cannot in good conscience

03:43.265 --> 03:45.184
continue to serve a leader
who recklessly puts marines

03:45.184 --> 03:46.894
in the line of fire
for her own gain.

03:46.894 --> 03:49.021
We were hunting a terrorist

03:49.021 --> 03:51.273
who had to be brought
to justice.

03:51.273 --> 03:52.650
We sent in a team
with limited intel

03:52.650 --> 03:53.734
and not enough time to prepare.

03:53.734 --> 03:55.235
My marines paid the price.

03:55.235 --> 03:58.364
Hindsight doesn't change what
we still need to accomplish.

03:58.364 --> 04:01.617
Twelve soldiers, dozens
of innocent civilians died

04:01.617 --> 04:02.910
to boost your poll numbers.

04:05.079 --> 04:08.332
You may be able
to justify your actions,

04:08.332 --> 04:09.541
but I cannot.

04:09.541 --> 04:16.131
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:16.131 --> 04:17.549
You're dismissed.

04:22.429 --> 04:25.849
[door click open and shut]

04:27.393 --> 04:34.400
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:38.904 --> 04:41.907
[indistinct chatter]

04:52.376 --> 04:54.336
Welcome to Medina Station.

04:54.336 --> 04:55.713
It's good to see you.

04:55.713 --> 04:56.922
[grunts]

04:56.922 --> 04:59.800
You promised
to hold your temper.

04:59.800 --> 05:00.718
I did.

05:02.678 --> 05:05.472
<i>Sabaka fo mama.</i>
You sold us out.

05:05.472 --> 05:07.182
You gave Marco's location
to the Earthers

05:07.182 --> 05:09.601
and got dozens
of innocent Belters killed.

05:09.601 --> 05:12.187
Marco rigged that ship to blow
and kill everyone.

05:12.187 --> 05:14.481
- He set us up.
- And you took the bait,

05:14.481 --> 05:17.067
blinded by your self-imposed
dependence on the Inners.

05:17.067 --> 05:19.820
You should be thanking me
for not sending you.

05:21.655 --> 05:25.784
Back-channeling our information
to the UN was the right move.

05:25.784 --> 05:29.038
It appeased the Earthers
and kept our hands clean

05:29.038 --> 05:32.207
in the eyes of the OPA factions
who supported Marco.

05:32.207 --> 05:34.626
Yeah, well,
Marco lied to our faces.

05:34.626 --> 05:36.837
The other factions
would have backed us.

05:36.837 --> 05:38.589
And the video
he is now broadcasting

05:38.589 --> 05:41.550
is going to rally thousands
of Belters to his side.

05:41.550 --> 05:43.594
And your bullshit statement
blaming the UN

05:43.594 --> 05:45.471
will rally thousands more.

05:45.471 --> 05:47.598
You turned Marco
into a goddamn hero.

05:47.598 --> 05:50.768
I trusted you with my vote,
and you chose to let him go.

05:50.768 --> 05:53.353
- I was cleaning up your mess.
- You're putting this on me?

05:53.353 --> 05:56.148
[Ashford] You weren't there.
She cast the right vote.

05:56.148 --> 05:58.859
She saw the larger picture
unfolding in that air lock

05:58.859 --> 06:01.779
and she made the correct
decision, difficult as it was.

06:01.779 --> 06:03.864
Which is exactly what I did.

06:03.864 --> 06:05.616
We were both
in impossible positions.

06:05.616 --> 06:06.909
No.
Truce or no truce,

06:06.909 --> 06:08.494
we <i>na</i> sell out our own
to the Inners.

06:08.494 --> 06:11.872
We all have enough blame
to share, eh,

06:11.872 --> 06:15.667
and even more problems to solve,
so politics be damned.

06:18.253 --> 06:20.172
The Inners are looking
for any way they can

06:20.172 --> 06:22.049
to control the Ring,
and we cannot let that happen.

06:22.049 --> 06:24.009
Which is why I'm here.

06:24.009 --> 06:25.761
I'm negotiating a way for us

06:25.761 --> 06:27.638
to maintain control
of the Ring Space

06:27.638 --> 06:30.516
and for the UNN
to remove their battleship.

06:31.558 --> 06:34.311
I used the information that you
gave me as a bargaining chip

06:34.311 --> 06:37.106
to keep the UN
out of our business.

06:37.106 --> 06:39.191
This station is the backbone

06:39.191 --> 06:41.318
of the Belt's economic future.

06:41.318 --> 06:44.196
We must do whatever have to
to protect it.

06:47.908 --> 06:50.160
You can do it without me.

06:50.160 --> 06:50.994
I quit.

06:52.579 --> 06:54.748
Aw, Drummer.

06:54.748 --> 06:56.375
[door whooshes]

06:56.375 --> 07:02.089
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:02.089 --> 07:05.092
[wind whooshing]

07:08.095 --> 07:15.102
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:17.813 --> 07:19.106
[Holden grunts]

07:20.732 --> 07:22.776
[Holden shouting]

07:22.776 --> 07:24.528
[grunting]

07:24.528 --> 07:27.614
[panting]

07:27.614 --> 07:28.949
[sighs heavily]

07:35.330 --> 07:38.333
<i>[ominous music]</i>

07:38.333 --> 07:44.214
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:44.214 --> 07:46.341
[device chirping]

07:48.635 --> 07:50.596
<i>[Holden] Hey.</i>
- How's it going down there?

07:50.596 --> 07:52.806
Another Belter wandered off.

07:53.891 --> 07:56.018
- Just found his body.
- Fuck.

07:56.018 --> 07:58.604
<i>[Holden] I told them
to stay in their spots.</i>

07:58.604 --> 08:01.273
They're blind, not deaf,
God damn it.

08:01.273 --> 08:02.983
<i>[Naomi]
You're doing all you can.</i>

08:02.983 --> 08:05.027
Nobody stands a chance
without you.

08:05.027 --> 08:06.904
Yeah.
[sighs]

08:06.904 --> 08:08.989
Well, at least tell me
your plan's working.

08:08.989 --> 08:11.783
They're building the cable
and the gantry.

08:11.783 --> 08:14.453
I'm finishing the <i>Roci's</i>
tensioning system.

08:14.453 --> 08:15.704
We'll be maneuvering
to match orbits

08:15.704 --> 08:17.831
<i>and make the hookup shortly.</i>

08:17.831 --> 08:19.541
Good.

08:19.541 --> 08:22.544
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

08:22.544 --> 08:24.755
One of us needs something
to go right.

08:26.924 --> 08:28.926
I'll let you know
when we connect the ships.

08:30.928 --> 08:32.137
Okay.

08:34.890 --> 08:35.891
[device beeps]

08:40.479 --> 08:42.022
[man coughs]

08:43.690 --> 08:46.276
Holden, that you?

08:47.194 --> 08:48.528
Yeah.

08:53.200 --> 08:54.952
Did you find Barrett?

08:56.703 --> 08:57.537
Yeah.

08:59.831 --> 09:02.876
- He's dead.
- [exhales] <i>Pashang.</i>

09:03.835 --> 09:05.254
I didn't think he would go.

09:05.254 --> 09:07.756
If you hear anyone else
wander off,

09:07.756 --> 09:09.967
yell, and I'll come.

09:09.967 --> 09:11.551
There are slugs
in every tunnel now.

09:11.551 --> 09:13.303
- Nowhere's safe.
[man] Get him off me!

09:13.303 --> 09:14.846
Get him off me!
Get him off!

09:14.846 --> 09:17.516
[Holden] Hey, hey, hey, hey.
Hey, hey, easy, easy.

09:17.516 --> 09:19.142
There's nothing there.
There's nothing there.

09:19.142 --> 09:20.644
There's nothing there.
Easy.

09:20.644 --> 09:21.478
[injector clicks]

09:24.273 --> 09:25.440
[injector clicks]

09:26.275 --> 09:29.278
[blowtorch whooshing]

09:43.625 --> 09:44.543
[Holden] Hey.

09:46.211 --> 09:47.587
You got them all.

09:51.675 --> 09:52.801
Amos?

09:54.386 --> 09:56.388
You got them all.
They're dead.

09:57.347 --> 10:00.142
I'm just sending a message
to the rest of them,

10:00.142 --> 10:02.144
make sure
they don't keep coming.

10:04.980 --> 10:07.024
- [blowtorch whooshing]
- Need me to get you anything?

10:08.775 --> 10:10.193
I'm good.

10:12.988 --> 10:15.282
Let me borrow the torch.
I might need it.

10:15.282 --> 10:17.284
I'm keeping it.

10:17.284 --> 10:23.957
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:36.470 --> 10:38.472
- [foot thudding]
- [slug squelching]

10:38.472 --> 10:40.557
Holden?

10:40.557 --> 10:41.767
Yeah.

10:41.767 --> 10:44.019
[machines blipping softly]

10:44.019 --> 10:46.980
What did the results say
after analyzing our friend?

10:46.980 --> 10:47.981
Well, you tell me.

10:51.443 --> 10:52.277
Yeah.

10:53.570 --> 10:55.614
Sample's primarily water

10:55.614 --> 10:58.575
and tridecyl
and "oli-ol" alcohols.

10:58.575 --> 11:00.577
Oleyl.
They're from the ocean.

11:00.577 --> 11:02.996
High concentrations
of R and S-2

11:02.996 --> 11:07.709
"propy-piper-dine
stereo-somers."

11:07.709 --> 11:11.046
Propylpiperidine stereoisomers,
the poison.

11:14.257 --> 11:16.843
"Benzo-pheno-nomes,"

11:16.843 --> 11:19.262
trace levels
of copper chromite.

11:20.430 --> 11:21.431
Close enough.

11:21.431 --> 11:23.350
It confirms my theory

11:23.350 --> 11:26.978
that the slugs secrete
a powerful neurotoxin

11:26.978 --> 11:30.190
that immediately
paralyzes humans

11:30.190 --> 11:33.235
and causes respiratory failure
upon contact with our skin.

11:33.235 --> 11:36.279
Anything in there about
some kind of possible vaccine?

11:36.279 --> 11:37.406
[sighs]

11:38.657 --> 11:41.326
Based on what you said,
with an unknown species

11:41.326 --> 11:43.954
and the equipment I have,
even if I could see,

11:43.954 --> 11:46.039
I maybe could come up
with something in a week?

11:46.039 --> 11:47.624
[Murtry] Murtry.

11:47.624 --> 11:50.168
What about treating the
organisms blinding everyone?

11:50.168 --> 11:51.545
Was there anything
in my blood?

11:51.545 --> 11:53.797
Nothing out of the ordinary.
I don't know.

11:53.797 --> 11:55.715
Maybe your immunity
has something to do

11:55.715 --> 11:57.717
with your multi-parent
genetics,

11:57.717 --> 11:59.261
but that still doesn't help us.

12:00.178 --> 12:01.805
There has to be
something we're missing.

12:01.805 --> 12:04.474
[Murtry] Understood.
Captain Holden?

12:09.229 --> 12:11.064
You rang?

12:11.064 --> 12:13.108
[Murtry] We've had an update
from the <i>Edward Israel.</i>

12:13.108 --> 12:14.943
They said tomorrow
the waters above us will have

12:14.943 --> 12:17.362
receded enough so that we can
build camp on the surface.

12:17.362 --> 12:18.697
Well, that's great,

12:18.697 --> 12:20.073
but I can't get everyone
out of here

12:20.073 --> 12:21.491
if I'm the only one
who can see.

12:21.491 --> 12:23.201
Well, my people
can handle the ropes

12:23.201 --> 12:24.870
if you can guide us out.

12:24.870 --> 12:27.664
I mean, even blind,
we'll be safer up there

12:27.664 --> 12:30.417
without these slugs
falling on us.

12:30.417 --> 12:33.086
We're not leaving
the Belters behind.

12:34.671 --> 12:36.506
I'm not asking you
to leave them.

12:36.506 --> 12:38.383
I'm asking you to help us.

12:39.384 --> 12:41.511
When we leave here,

12:41.511 --> 12:43.180
we're all leaving together.

12:44.431 --> 12:47.684
In the land of the blind,
the one-eyed man is king.

12:47.684 --> 12:51.563
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

12:51.563 --> 12:55.192
I'm gonna take the Belters
to the latrine.

12:55.192 --> 12:57.527
Then I'm gonna come back

12:57.527 --> 12:59.988
and I'll do the same
for your people.

13:01.781 --> 13:03.200
Thank you, Captain.

13:03.200 --> 13:09.706
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:19.674 --> 13:22.052
What are you doing up so early?

13:22.052 --> 13:24.095
[sighs] I'm sorry.
I gotta go.

13:25.013 --> 13:27.015
If this is a "love 'em
and leave 'em" situation,

13:27.015 --> 13:28.808
just know you're gonna
miss out on waffles.

13:28.808 --> 13:30.185
I'll grab a coffee
downstairs.

13:30.185 --> 13:31.770
They got pancakes, too,
if that's more your thing.

13:34.272 --> 13:35.690
What's the rush?

13:37.442 --> 13:38.568
I got a job interview.

13:39.236 --> 13:40.779
Oh.

13:40.779 --> 13:42.531
You didn't mention anything
last night.

13:42.531 --> 13:43.949
Yeah, um...

13:45.659 --> 13:48.537
...ice mining out on Europa.

13:48.537 --> 13:50.539
They say it could be
a minimum ten-month job.

13:50.539 --> 13:53.208
Wow. [laughs softly]
Congratulations.

13:53.208 --> 13:55.210
I don't know if it's
for sure yet, but, uh,

13:55.210 --> 13:57.337
I didn't say anything 'cause I
didn't want to ruin any of this.

13:57.337 --> 13:59.381
You're not ruining anything.

14:00.632 --> 14:02.008
All right.

14:02.008 --> 14:03.843
Well, thanks
for being cool about it.

14:03.843 --> 14:05.262
Mm.
[laughs softly]

14:11.476 --> 14:13.228
How about we do waffles
tonight?

14:13.228 --> 14:14.729
Yeah, sure.

14:14.729 --> 14:16.690
All right.

14:18.191 --> 14:19.776
[door clicks open]

14:21.987 --> 14:23.405
[door clicks shut]

14:25.407 --> 14:27.242
[Esai] Ship's on its way in
from Callisto.

14:27.242 --> 14:30.078
The off-loaded cargo's being
housed in storage level three

14:30.078 --> 14:32.497
and is scheduled
for immediate recycling.

14:32.497 --> 14:34.249
Where are we
on those access codes?

14:34.249 --> 14:36.376
- Should have them by tonight.
- The right ones this time?

14:36.376 --> 14:39.129
- Go fuck yourself.
- Do we have a buyer?

14:39.129 --> 14:40.338
[Beltran]
It's already been arranged.

14:40.338 --> 14:41.631
We're just escorting
the package

14:41.631 --> 14:43.883
from the dock storage facility
to one of the berths.

14:43.883 --> 14:45.343
So we're just
the middlemen on this?

14:45.343 --> 14:47.178
All we have to do
is babysit the package

14:47.178 --> 14:48.346
until we make the handoff.

14:48.346 --> 14:49.347
- That's it?
[Esai] That's it.

14:49.347 --> 14:50.682
And each of our shares on this

14:50.682 --> 14:53.560
is almost ten times what we made
on the terraforming job.

14:53.560 --> 14:54.936
Holy shit.

14:54.936 --> 14:57.647
[indistinct chatter]

14:57.647 --> 14:58.857
What's the package?

14:58.857 --> 15:01.234
I wasn't provided
with that information.

15:01.234 --> 15:03.737
For the money we're getting,
it doesn't matter.

15:03.737 --> 15:06.448
You mean we're getting paid not
to ask questions, is that it?

15:07.198 --> 15:09.117
- Is that a problem?
- I'm fine with that.

15:12.162 --> 15:13.371
Good.

15:13.371 --> 15:16.207
I'll give you all
instructions tomorrow.

15:20.587 --> 15:22.505
If easy money
isn't your thing,

15:22.505 --> 15:25.342
three-way split's
better than four, so...

15:30.430 --> 15:33.433
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

15:33.433 --> 15:40.440
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:41.900 --> 15:43.360
So this will keep the cable
from breaking

15:43.360 --> 15:45.278
while the <i>Roci</i> is pulling?

15:45.278 --> 15:47.656
This and the one Felcia's
building on the <i>Barb</i>

15:47.656 --> 15:49.157
should keep it taut.

15:49.157 --> 15:50.909
[wheel stops whirring]

15:51.868 --> 15:54.204
If the cable goes slack

15:54.204 --> 15:56.706
and tightens too fast,

15:56.706 --> 15:59.000
the stress will snap it.

15:59.000 --> 16:01.252
If that happened,
would we still have time

16:01.252 --> 16:03.421
to bring everyone
from the <i>Barb</i> here?

16:05.256 --> 16:07.509
Hey, Naomi,
we're approaching the <i>Barb.</i>

16:07.509 --> 16:09.260
It is time for us
to make our way down.

16:11.554 --> 16:12.722
I'm gonna be pumping
the brakes.

16:12.722 --> 16:14.182
Y'all are gonna feel this
a bit,

16:14.182 --> 16:16.309
<i>so make sure everything
is locked down and secure.</i>

16:16.309 --> 16:18.186
Copy that.
We're good.

16:18.186 --> 16:19.938
- [button clicks]
- Here we go.

16:19.938 --> 16:22.941
[engines whooshing]

16:22.941 --> 16:25.944
<i>[tense music]</i>

16:25.944 --> 16:32.951
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:38.039 --> 16:41.167
[soft creaking]

16:41.167 --> 16:43.962
[cable whirring]

16:43.962 --> 16:46.089
We're out of mining net.

16:46.089 --> 16:47.966
Cable just 800 meter.

16:47.966 --> 16:49.300
No safety margin.

16:49.300 --> 16:51.094
Sure your math right, <i>ke?</i>

16:51.094 --> 16:52.303
It right.

16:52.303 --> 16:54.264
We make it work.
We have to.

16:54.264 --> 16:56.266
I meant to tell you
this sooner.

16:56.266 --> 16:58.101
Thanks for hating
your parents.

16:58.101 --> 17:00.145
You might save us all
from being fucked.

17:00.145 --> 17:02.564
[chuckles]

17:02.564 --> 17:05.567
[welding torch fizzing]

17:11.573 --> 17:14.159
I'm gonna grab some more
sedatives and painkillers.

17:16.661 --> 17:18.830
How are the Belters
holding up?

17:18.830 --> 17:20.832
I hear the slugs
got some of them.

17:20.832 --> 17:22.917
[Holden] Without the meds,
a lot more would be dead.

17:24.544 --> 17:25.837
We only have one left.

17:27.046 --> 17:28.631
Can your pharmaceutical printer
make more?

17:28.631 --> 17:30.592
[machine chirps]

17:30.592 --> 17:33.344
I don't have the reagents
for those kinds of drugs.

17:33.344 --> 17:35.346
[sighs] Shit.

17:35.346 --> 17:37.348
We're giving you food and meds
to help the Belters,

17:37.348 --> 17:39.225
but at some point,
we're gonna run out.

17:39.225 --> 17:41.269
We're gonna have
to cut our losses.

17:41.269 --> 17:42.687
Belters aren't gonna forget

17:42.687 --> 17:44.856
you're the reason
we're down here.

17:44.856 --> 17:46.232
<i>[ominous music]</i>

17:46.232 --> 17:47.442
[Carol] Holden!
[man] Holden!

17:47.442 --> 17:48.777
[Carol] Holden!

17:48.777 --> 17:52.113
[Belters chattering
indistinctly]

17:52.113 --> 17:53.323
What?
What happened?

17:53.323 --> 17:55.158
I think someone walked away...
that way.

17:58.578 --> 18:00.205
Shit.

18:03.041 --> 18:04.083
Amos!

18:05.794 --> 18:07.003
Amos?

18:09.172 --> 18:10.006
Amos.

18:11.382 --> 18:12.383
[flashlight clicks]

18:12.383 --> 18:16.429
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:16.429 --> 18:20.058
Amos...step back.

18:26.356 --> 18:27.690
Listen to me.

18:29.567 --> 18:31.194
Say something.

18:31.194 --> 18:33.279
- [shouting]
- Fuck, Jesus Christ!

18:33.279 --> 18:35.156
Amos, stop!

18:39.035 --> 18:42.038
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

18:42.038 --> 18:43.957
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:43.957 --> 18:46.334
[softly]
Okay.

18:46.334 --> 18:52.841
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:00.557 --> 19:02.433
All right.

19:02.433 --> 19:04.185
I got you.
It's all right.

19:04.185 --> 19:06.145
It's all right.

19:10.316 --> 19:12.318
[woman] Someone coming.

19:12.318 --> 19:14.237
[indistinct chatter]

19:14.237 --> 19:15.905
Here, watch your leg.

19:15.905 --> 19:17.907
- [Jakob] Holden?
- Yeah.

19:23.872 --> 19:25.123
Amos.

19:26.791 --> 19:28.293
Amos, look at me.

19:29.377 --> 19:30.753
Look at me.

19:33.464 --> 19:35.717
As long as
we're still breathing,

19:35.717 --> 19:37.093
we're alive,

19:38.970 --> 19:41.014
I can't lose you.

19:41.014 --> 19:47.854
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:55.570 --> 19:56.988
[faint metallic thunk]

19:56.988 --> 19:58.823
[footsteps approaching]

19:58.823 --> 20:00.033
[Ashford]
I've been looking for you.

20:00.033 --> 20:02.118
I checked every bar
in the station.

20:03.870 --> 20:07.081
I drink when I'm angry,
not when I'm sad.

20:07.081 --> 20:10.793
Drummer, I understand
why you quit,

20:10.793 --> 20:13.671
but you can't let
your sorrows drown you.

20:14.923 --> 20:17.508
Fred Johnson should have
let us handle our own business,

20:17.508 --> 20:19.302
no doubt,

20:19.302 --> 20:22.138
but he isn't wrong
about this place.

20:22.138 --> 20:23.973
We need it,

20:23.973 --> 20:26.476
and we need the Inners

20:26.476 --> 20:28.853
if we want a future of peace.

20:28.853 --> 20:32.231
[sighs heavily]

20:32.231 --> 20:34.859
The Mormon pictures
in my office

20:34.859 --> 20:37.445
always made me laugh,

20:37.445 --> 20:41.366
celebrating
the pride of the Inners,

20:41.366 --> 20:43.576
a history of coveting
another's homeland

20:43.576 --> 20:45.203
and killing to take it.

20:46.287 --> 20:49.082
I believed in Fred's vision
for an independent Belt,

20:49.082 --> 20:52.627
but now that we're free,

20:52.627 --> 20:55.964
we're painting
those same pictures,

20:55.964 --> 20:58.800
murdering innocent people,
our own people,

20:58.800 --> 21:02.261
in exchange for peace

21:02.261 --> 21:03.888
with the Inners.

21:06.474 --> 21:08.935
I hope Marco is wrong
about our future,

21:08.935 --> 21:10.979
but I fear he's not.

21:12.689 --> 21:14.816
Eh, Marco is a nihilist...

21:14.816 --> 21:18.820
[stammers]
...in the guise of a patriot.

21:18.820 --> 21:21.406
His way is not the way forward
for the Belt.

21:21.406 --> 21:22.740
And this is?

21:23.950 --> 21:26.285
I have seen blood spilled
my entire life

21:26.285 --> 21:29.288
and I have spilled enough myself
to know that the future,

21:29.288 --> 21:31.416
our future,

21:31.416 --> 21:33.126
cannot be built on violence.

21:33.126 --> 21:34.711
You sound like a politician.

21:34.711 --> 21:36.921
[chuckles]

21:36.921 --> 21:39.966
No, I'm just old.

21:39.966 --> 21:42.969
Age changes you
in ways you don't expect.

21:44.721 --> 21:48.558
[chuckles] My focus isn't
as narrow as it once was.

21:50.768 --> 21:53.354
Fred offer you the job
of running this place, <i>ke?</i>

21:53.354 --> 21:56.399
Yeah, he did.

21:56.399 --> 21:57.817
But I declined.

21:57.817 --> 22:00.945
- I have more pressing matters.
- Like what?

22:00.945 --> 22:05.324
I am going to hunt down Marco
and kill him.

22:05.324 --> 22:07.744
Interesting way to start
a future of peace.

22:07.744 --> 22:09.537
Well, the longer
Marco lives,

22:09.537 --> 22:11.122
the more followers
he will recruit,

22:11.122 --> 22:15.418
and the more our nation
and our peace will be at risk.

22:17.837 --> 22:20.798
And I also admit I am eager
to see his pretty face

22:20.798 --> 22:22.717
floating outside the air lock.

22:24.677 --> 22:26.554
[laughs softly]

22:26.554 --> 22:28.556
[both chuckle]

22:28.556 --> 22:31.225
I see age hasn't
changed everything.

22:31.225 --> 22:34.854
[both laugh]

22:34.854 --> 22:38.733
You know, for this mission,
I am going to need a good XO.

22:40.777 --> 22:43.905
The job is yours...

22:43.905 --> 22:45.364
if you want it.

22:46.491 --> 22:50.912
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:59.212 --> 23:01.214
[muffled doorbell rings]

23:06.886 --> 23:09.013
Can I help you?

23:09.013 --> 23:10.807
Uh, I'm...I'm sorry.

23:10.807 --> 23:12.391
I'm looking for Esai Martin.

23:12.391 --> 23:13.810
[Esai] Who is it, honey?

23:13.810 --> 23:15.770
[Katlin] Esai.
- Hey.

23:15.770 --> 23:17.146
Hey.

23:17.146 --> 23:18.731
Come on in.

23:18.731 --> 23:20.149
[laughs softly]

23:21.400 --> 23:22.360
[door clicks shut]

23:22.360 --> 23:24.487
Bobbie, this is my wife,
Katlin.

23:24.487 --> 23:25.738
Katlin, this is Bobbie.

23:25.738 --> 23:27.865
She does consulting
with the department.

23:27.865 --> 23:29.283
Oh, it's nice to meet you.

23:29.283 --> 23:31.661
- You too.
[Emily] Stop it!

23:31.661 --> 23:33.788
- Ow! Mom!
- Excuse me.

23:33.788 --> 23:35.957
[Charlie] Emily pushed me!
[Emily] Charlie's cheating.

23:35.957 --> 23:37.166
- It's bedtime.
[Charlie] No!

23:37.166 --> 23:38.960
- Can I get you a drink?
- I'm good.

23:38.960 --> 23:40.545
- Thank you.
[Katlin] Come on.

23:40.545 --> 23:42.213
[Katlin] Let's go.
[kids] Fine.

23:42.213 --> 23:46.259
These little rascals,
that's Charlie and Emily.

23:46.259 --> 23:48.636
[Charlie]
Can you read us a story?

23:48.636 --> 23:49.929
[door clicks shut]

23:49.929 --> 23:52.140
I'm so sorry.
I didn't know you had a family.

23:52.140 --> 23:54.350
Why would you?
What's going on?

23:54.350 --> 23:57.186
It's about the job.
Something's not right.

23:57.186 --> 23:59.730
It's too easy and there are
too many unknowns.

23:59.730 --> 24:02.191
We're not walking away.

24:02.191 --> 24:04.819
- Did Beltran bring this to you?
- He did, yeah.

24:04.819 --> 24:06.195
I don't trust him.

24:06.195 --> 24:07.822
He's active military,
isn't he?

24:13.286 --> 24:15.454
I told you I'm not gonna
help you move weapons

24:15.454 --> 24:17.206
or anything
that will hurt people.

24:17.206 --> 24:18.875
Beltran said
there was nothing lethal.

24:18.875 --> 24:21.711
- But you don't know for sure?
- [plates clink]

24:23.212 --> 24:24.547
You're smarter than this.

24:24.547 --> 24:26.966
You don't do any job
without knowing the details.

24:26.966 --> 24:28.176
What's going on?

24:28.176 --> 24:30.720
[sighs]

24:30.720 --> 24:32.180
If I take this job,

24:32.180 --> 24:33.764
I'll make enough money
to leave.

24:33.764 --> 24:36.100
Leave?
And go where?

24:36.100 --> 24:38.561
The Ring Gate, new worlds.

24:38.561 --> 24:41.022
Colony ships are lining up
already to go through.

24:41.022 --> 24:43.024
After this job,
I can buy my whole family

24:43.024 --> 24:45.193
a place on board
one of those ships.

24:45.193 --> 24:46.402
No one's allowed
through the blockade.

24:46.402 --> 24:47.737
For now,

24:47.737 --> 24:49.572
but once it's lifted,
the floodgates will open.

24:49.572 --> 24:50.865
I don't want
to be stranded here.

24:50.865 --> 24:52.033
What are you talking about?

24:52.033 --> 24:53.910
Those planets are habitable.

24:53.910 --> 24:56.996
There's no reason why Mars
should continue terraforming.

24:56.996 --> 24:59.498
Mars has been terraforming
for generations.

24:59.498 --> 25:01.876
It's a part of our culture.
We're not gonna abandon it.

25:01.876 --> 25:05.046
You think all those scientists
and engineers are gonna keep

25:05.046 --> 25:06.505
creating an atmosphere
that won't be finished

25:06.505 --> 25:08.174
for another century

25:08.174 --> 25:09.967
when they can go work
on another planet already

25:09.967 --> 25:11.510
with air they can breathe?

25:11.510 --> 25:14.263
And when the best
and brightest start leaving,

25:14.263 --> 25:16.766
it's gonna be just people like
you and me left on this rock.

25:16.766 --> 25:18.517
Mars is changing.
It's not dead.

25:18.517 --> 25:22.271
Mars died the moment they
discovered those new worlds.

25:23.356 --> 25:26.275
I wasn't smart enough to be
on the terraforming project,

25:26.275 --> 25:28.444
and the military
didn't want me, but...

25:28.444 --> 25:29.862
it didn't matter.

25:29.862 --> 25:31.739
I did my duty

25:31.739 --> 25:34.951
because Mars promised
a garden for everyone.

25:34.951 --> 25:37.703
I was a good Martian
my entire life

25:37.703 --> 25:39.538
because I wanted my children

25:39.538 --> 25:41.290
to get their share
of the rewards.

25:41.290 --> 25:43.709
Well, one way or another,

25:43.709 --> 25:46.671
I'm gonna make sure
they get what they deserve.

25:46.671 --> 25:50.007
You can't get your family
off the planet if you're dead.

25:50.007 --> 25:52.468
- [door clicks open]
[Katlin] Esai.

25:52.468 --> 25:54.053
They want you
to read to them tonight.

25:54.053 --> 25:56.138
Oh.
Uh, tell them I'll be right in.

25:56.138 --> 25:58.140
- [Katlin] Okay.
- Okay, thanks, babe.

26:01.310 --> 26:03.312
If you want out, just say so.

26:03.312 --> 26:05.523
You don't owe me
anything anymore.

26:05.523 --> 26:12.280
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:16.951 --> 26:18.202
Amos?

26:19.620 --> 26:20.913
Amos?

26:20.913 --> 26:22.999
Here.

26:22.999 --> 26:24.417
I'm here.

26:24.417 --> 26:27.420
[indistinct chatter]

26:30.548 --> 26:32.341
Holden told me what happened.

26:33.843 --> 26:35.761
I know how you feel.

26:35.761 --> 26:38.306
No, you don't.

26:40.474 --> 26:42.435
It's okay if you're scared.

26:45.855 --> 26:47.815
I don't know what I am.

26:49.692 --> 26:53.612
When I was five,
I lived in a basement.

26:53.612 --> 26:56.490
And I'd have nightmares,

26:56.490 --> 26:58.242
and when I woke up
and opened my eyes,

26:58.242 --> 27:00.244
everything was still black.

27:00.244 --> 27:04.332
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:04.332 --> 27:06.167
That's when they came in.

27:06.167 --> 27:11.380
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:11.380 --> 27:14.633
I thought I was dead

27:14.633 --> 27:17.053
and there was nothing
I could do about it.

27:19.430 --> 27:20.848
There's nothing we can do now

27:20.848 --> 27:23.768
except sit in the dark
and wait to die.

27:23.768 --> 27:28.147
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:28.147 --> 27:31.233
People like us deserve a say
in how we go out.

27:34.111 --> 27:36.072
That's all I ever wanted.

27:38.574 --> 27:42.161
- [grunting]
- [loud thunking]

27:42.161 --> 27:44.163
- [Holden sighs]
- [indistinct chatter]

27:44.163 --> 27:46.165
[shovel clatters loudly]

27:52.880 --> 27:55.424
Holden, what happened?
Are you okay?

27:57.093 --> 27:58.928
[sighs]

27:58.928 --> 28:00.346
My friend.

28:03.474 --> 28:04.809
Is he dead?

28:06.310 --> 28:07.937
No.

28:09.480 --> 28:12.858
There has to be some reason
why I can still see.

28:15.820 --> 28:17.571
I'm gonna take
another blood sample.

28:17.571 --> 28:19.532
No, we've taken
two blood samples.

28:19.532 --> 28:21.951
There...
there is nothing abnormal.

28:21.951 --> 28:24.662
- I can't let us die down here.
- It's not on you.

28:24.662 --> 28:26.705
Yes, it is.

28:26.705 --> 28:29.834
- It's on me.
- [latches clicking]

28:37.508 --> 28:38.801
What if it's not your blood?

28:38.801 --> 28:40.219
What if your blood
is normal

28:40.219 --> 28:43.431
but it's your vitreous humor
that isn't?

28:43.431 --> 28:46.142
- My what?
- Your eye fluid.

28:46.142 --> 28:48.018
What can we do to find out?

28:48.018 --> 28:52.857
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:52.857 --> 28:55.734
[syringe whirs]

28:55.734 --> 28:57.319
And this is the only way?

28:57.319 --> 29:00.614
We only need a little fluid
to analyze.

29:00.614 --> 29:02.450
Just don't go in too far.

29:02.450 --> 29:03.701
Good safety tip.

29:05.453 --> 29:07.371
[inhales sharply]

29:07.371 --> 29:09.206
[exhales deeply]

29:09.206 --> 29:13.461
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:13.461 --> 29:16.255
- [gasps]
- [syringe whirs]

29:16.255 --> 29:18.716
- All right, I got some.
- Oh, good.

29:18.716 --> 29:20.384
Okay, put the sample
in the machine.

29:22.553 --> 29:23.762
[exhales sharply]

29:24.680 --> 29:26.265
So how long do you think
it's gonna take until...

29:26.265 --> 29:29.477
[machine blipping]

29:29.477 --> 29:32.438
That was quick.
Is that a good or a bad sign?

29:32.438 --> 29:34.148
I don't know.
What does the screen say?

29:35.900 --> 29:39.236
Uh, glucose concentration
3.1 millimoles per liter.

29:39.236 --> 29:42.281
"Liptides" 1.97 micrograms
per milliliter.

29:42.281 --> 29:43.741
Estimated total protein,

29:43.741 --> 29:47.870
1580 with trace
dysplastic metabolites.

29:47.870 --> 29:49.663
[scoffs, laughs]

29:49.663 --> 29:51.373
What?
What's so funny?

29:51.373 --> 29:55.461
Uh, well, nothing is...
is really abnormal,

29:55.461 --> 29:58.088
but if we end up
getting out of here,

29:58.088 --> 29:59.757
you might want to see a doctor.

29:59.757 --> 30:01.592
You have precancerous cells
that could become

30:01.592 --> 30:03.677
life-threatening
if not treated.

30:05.054 --> 30:06.764
Well, I already knew that.

30:08.098 --> 30:11.852
I was irradiated on Eros,
so I'm full of oncocidals.

30:17.566 --> 30:19.944
- Thanks.
- No, I don't want your hand.

30:21.028 --> 30:22.947
- You have a medication port.
- Yeah.

30:22.947 --> 30:24.865
I've had to take
regular injections.

30:26.700 --> 30:30.538
The anticancer meds are what
is killing the organisms.

30:30.538 --> 30:32.748
<i>[hopeful music]</i>

30:32.748 --> 30:34.750
That's what's making me immune?

30:34.750 --> 30:38.128
It has to be the abnormality
we are looking for.

30:38.128 --> 30:40.214
Do you have the reagents
to make the meds?

30:40.214 --> 30:42.550
I think so.
I think so.

30:42.550 --> 30:45.261
I just need you to read
some information off your patch

30:45.261 --> 30:48.097
and help me gather up
some chemicals.

30:48.097 --> 30:49.932
- [exhales heavily]
- [laughs softly]

30:51.976 --> 30:54.562
It's been a while
since I've seen you smile.

30:54.562 --> 30:57.022
[laughs]

31:16.125 --> 31:20.170
It's a tragedy when anyone dies
in the line of duty.

31:20.170 --> 31:25.134
But these 12 heroes
we're honoring today

31:25.134 --> 31:29.263
died to spare our planet
from further tragedy.

31:29.263 --> 31:31.890
Service above self

31:31.890 --> 31:34.018
is what makes our soldiers

31:34.018 --> 31:35.978
the most noble

31:35.978 --> 31:38.564
and honorable people
on our planet.

31:38.564 --> 31:41.859
They are the symbols
of who we are as a people,

31:41.859 --> 31:45.696
and the ideals
we fight to defend.

31:46.822 --> 31:49.074
[soft indistinct chatter]

31:51.076 --> 31:52.661
[sighs heavily]

31:57.916 --> 32:00.294
I'm sorry.
Memorials are never easy.

32:00.294 --> 32:02.296
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

32:02.296 --> 32:05.674
And how impersonal they are
makes them even worse.

32:05.674 --> 32:11.847
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:11.847 --> 32:15.851
I know each of these marines
was special to you,

32:15.851 --> 32:20.898
but I don't know why;
only you do.

32:20.898 --> 32:24.318
So nothing I say
to you today matters,

32:24.318 --> 32:25.903
and it shouldn't,

32:25.903 --> 32:30.574
because there are no words for
what these people meant to you.

32:33.827 --> 32:37.247
My son, Charanpal,
was a marine.

32:38.332 --> 32:41.168
He was also killed by the OPA.

32:41.168 --> 32:44.421
When he died,
all I wanted to know was,

32:44.421 --> 32:46.090
who was responsible?

32:46.090 --> 32:49.093
Who was the person
I could hate?

32:51.095 --> 32:52.930
But there was no one.

32:57.434 --> 33:00.312
The OPA killed your husbands,

33:00.312 --> 33:02.439
your wives,

33:02.439 --> 33:04.733
your parents,

33:04.733 --> 33:06.610
your children,

33:06.610 --> 33:09.822
but it is my fault
that they died.

33:10.906 --> 33:14.368
My job is to keep the people
of this planet safe,

33:14.368 --> 33:17.705
and I failed to do that
for your loved ones.

33:17.705 --> 33:19.790
I failed all of you,

33:19.790 --> 33:23.544
as a mother and as a leader...

33:23.544 --> 33:30.008
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:30.008 --> 33:32.261
...so know that I am to blame.

33:34.680 --> 33:37.891
And I understand
how all of you feel.

33:40.394 --> 33:43.272
And all I can say is,

33:43.272 --> 33:46.692
I am truly sorry.

33:46.692 --> 33:53.031
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:53.031 --> 33:56.034
[soft indistinct chatter]

34:00.330 --> 34:07.337
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:09.590 --> 34:11.925
[indistinct chatter]

34:11.925 --> 34:14.928
[indistinct announcement
over P.A. system]

34:16.305 --> 34:19.224
[boy] Yeah, throw it.

34:19.224 --> 34:20.267
David?

34:21.852 --> 34:23.645
- Hey.
[David] Oh, hey.

34:23.645 --> 34:25.439
Hey, Bobbie.

34:26.231 --> 34:27.983
- How you doing?
- I'm good.

34:27.983 --> 34:30.944
Good. Just busy.

34:30.944 --> 34:33.822
- How are things with you?
- Yeah, um...yeah, I'm fine.

34:35.324 --> 34:36.658
That's good.

34:36.658 --> 34:40.788
Do you wanna grab a beer,
sit down and talk?

34:40.788 --> 34:42.414
Love to, but I can't.

34:42.414 --> 34:44.416
I got an orientation meeting
I gotta get to.

34:44.416 --> 34:45.834
What for?

34:48.170 --> 34:50.506
I got placed
in the terraforming project.

34:50.506 --> 34:52.341
[laughs softly]

34:52.341 --> 34:54.927
Got the third-highest score on
the chemical engineering exam.

34:54.927 --> 34:56.595
[laughs softly]

34:56.595 --> 34:58.055
That's great.

34:58.055 --> 35:00.224
I'm happy for you.

35:00.224 --> 35:01.642
Thanks.

35:01.642 --> 35:05.854
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:05.854 --> 35:08.148
You know, I, um...

35:08.148 --> 35:09.942
I never got to say thank you

35:09.942 --> 35:12.486
for everything
that you did for me.

35:12.486 --> 35:14.905
Would've never gotten this job
if it wasn't for you.

35:15.739 --> 35:17.241
I'm doing my duty for Mars.

35:18.116 --> 35:19.535
Yeah. [laughs softly]

35:22.204 --> 35:24.498
Look, I...I'll see you around?
We could talk then?

35:24.498 --> 35:25.916
Of course.

35:26.750 --> 35:28.126
See you.

35:28.126 --> 35:32.422
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:37.219 --> 35:38.679
[door clicks open]

35:38.679 --> 35:39.763
[Thomas] I'm not sure
what kind of toppings

35:39.763 --> 35:41.849
you like on your waffles,

35:41.849 --> 35:43.725
so I just got everything.

35:43.725 --> 35:45.477
[sniffs]

35:46.728 --> 35:48.939
Butter, syrup.

35:48.939 --> 35:50.983
- Ice cream, whipped cream.
- Did you get the job?

35:52.568 --> 35:54.111
That wasn't a topping choice.

35:54.111 --> 35:55.696
Mm.

35:55.696 --> 35:59.074
- Let's eat and we'll talk.
- So that's a yes, then.

36:01.869 --> 36:03.078
Yeah.

36:03.078 --> 36:05.080
I leave next week.

36:05.080 --> 36:07.165
Good for you, but if you're
in such a rush to leave,

36:07.165 --> 36:08.625
you should probably
just go now.

36:08.625 --> 36:10.586
- Oh, don't do this.
- I'm not doing anything.

36:10.586 --> 36:11.920
You're the one leaving.

36:13.839 --> 36:15.674
Right. I get it.

36:15.674 --> 36:18.093
- Hating me is much easier.
- You don't know me.

36:19.219 --> 36:20.387
I don't?

36:22.556 --> 36:25.017
I want you to come with me.

36:25.017 --> 36:27.603
- What?
- Come to Europa with me.

36:27.603 --> 36:28.770
Oh, hang on.

36:28.770 --> 36:30.772
- I can't just up and leave.
- Why not?

36:30.772 --> 36:32.441
This give us a chance
to start over.

36:32.441 --> 36:33.984
What do you mean, start over?

36:33.984 --> 36:35.444
Come on, Bobbie.
I'm not stupid.

36:35.444 --> 36:37.070
I mean, I see the...
the new clothes,

36:37.070 --> 36:39.239
the fancy hotel room,
the room service.

36:39.239 --> 36:42.242
I know you're not doing
consulting work.

36:42.242 --> 36:43.827
Listen, I'm not judging you,
all right?

36:43.827 --> 36:45.621
I know we all gotta do
what we gotta do to get by.

36:45.621 --> 36:48.498
I'm just saying I know
this is not who you really are.

36:48.498 --> 36:49.917
Oh, yeah, that's what you know?

36:49.917 --> 36:51.335
So you think I need to be
fucking saved, is that it?

36:51.335 --> 36:53.003
- That's not what I'm saying.
- You don't get it.

36:53.003 --> 36:54.546
You're still
buying into the bullshit.

36:54.546 --> 36:57.633
Look around you.
The dream of Mars is dying.

36:57.633 --> 36:59.051
So stealing and getting yours,
that's the answer?

37:00.928 --> 37:02.346
[sighs]

37:04.014 --> 37:05.807
[sighs]

37:05.807 --> 37:07.434
What the hell happened?

37:09.978 --> 37:12.397
Everything we've ever fought for
has been for nothing.

37:13.357 --> 37:14.775
You really believe that?

37:23.992 --> 37:26.536
Go. Do the job.

37:26.536 --> 37:27.788
Be a good Martian.

37:27.788 --> 37:29.581
See what's here
when you get back.

37:29.581 --> 37:31.375
I will.

37:31.375 --> 37:33.168
And I hope
you're still here too.

37:39.007 --> 37:40.300
[door clicks shut]

37:41.969 --> 37:44.054
[bottle clatters]

37:45.639 --> 37:48.642
[structure whirring]

37:50.769 --> 37:54.523
And double the ammunition stores
for both PDCs.

37:54.523 --> 37:57.401
Marco's ship has
a lot of missiles.

37:57.401 --> 37:59.653
I'd hate to die because
we couldn't shoot back.

37:59.653 --> 38:00.821
<i>[man] Copy that.</i>

38:02.364 --> 38:03.991
[indistinct radio chatter]

38:03.991 --> 38:07.202
Requesting permission
to come aboard, Captain.

38:07.202 --> 38:08.912
Permission granted.

38:08.912 --> 38:10.330
[laughs]

38:13.959 --> 38:15.002
[chair whirs]

38:17.713 --> 38:19.756
A gift for you.

38:19.756 --> 38:23.093
Oh, that's very thoughtful.

38:23.093 --> 38:24.845
Oh, thank you.

38:24.845 --> 38:28.306
Well, we should probably toast
the crew before we set off.

38:28.306 --> 38:30.767
<i>Im</i> a gift for your send-off.

38:31.852 --> 38:33.270
You're not coming?

38:35.647 --> 38:37.357
I've worked for both
Anderson Dawes

38:37.357 --> 38:38.817
and Fred Johnson,

38:38.817 --> 38:40.986
big men with big dreams.

38:42.362 --> 38:44.322
And what are you
going to do, then?

38:46.783 --> 38:48.410
[scoffs softly]

38:48.410 --> 38:50.370
Stay out of politics.

38:53.165 --> 38:54.958
Well, then will you
do me a favor?

38:54.958 --> 38:56.543
Hmm?

38:56.543 --> 38:59.337
Hold on to this
until I finish the mission.

38:59.337 --> 39:01.882
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:01.882 --> 39:03.884
<i>Tenye wa chesh gut.</i>

39:03.884 --> 39:10.390
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:10.390 --> 39:11.933
[chuckles]

39:11.933 --> 39:18.940
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:28.950 --> 39:31.953
[thrusters whooshing]

39:31.953 --> 39:34.956
<i>[tense music]</i>

39:34.956 --> 39:36.374
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:36.374 --> 39:39.377
[welding torch fizzing]

39:39.377 --> 39:42.881
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:42.881 --> 39:45.217
<i>[Alex] Naomi,
the</i> Roci's <i>in position.</i>

39:45.217 --> 39:47.094
<i>Orbits are synced.
How's it coming out there?</i>

39:47.094 --> 39:49.513
Just finishing up
welding the gantry.

39:50.555 --> 39:52.099
Radio the <i>Barb</i>
and ready the drone.

39:52.099 --> 39:53.266
Copy that.

39:53.266 --> 39:58.980
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:58.980 --> 40:01.358
<i>Felcia, is the cable ready?</i>

40:01.358 --> 40:03.902
- All set and ready to go.
<i>[Alex] Roger that.</i>

40:03.902 --> 40:06.029
Hookup is on its way.

40:08.323 --> 40:11.326
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

40:11.326 --> 40:18.041
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:20.836 --> 40:24.131
[drone whirs]

40:26.925 --> 40:28.969
[cable clicks]

40:30.762 --> 40:31.972
Cable's secure.

40:31.972 --> 40:34.015
Thank you kindly.
Bringing her home.

40:34.015 --> 40:36.685
[thrusters whooshing]

40:36.685 --> 40:43.692
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:00.417 --> 41:03.086
Got it, Alex.
You can lose the drone.

41:03.086 --> 41:10.093
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:30.488 --> 41:32.324
[latch clicks]

41:35.118 --> 41:37.329
[touch screen beeping]

41:37.329 --> 41:38.914
Winch activated.

41:38.914 --> 41:42.042
[machine whirring]

41:47.130 --> 41:49.633
Okay, Alex, we're set.

41:49.633 --> 41:51.676
- Cable's connected.
<i>[Alex] Copy that.</i>

41:51.676 --> 41:54.387
I'm gonna give her
a little thrust.

41:54.387 --> 41:55.680
Hang tight.

41:55.680 --> 42:02.687
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:02.687 --> 42:04.731
Here goes nothing.

42:04.731 --> 42:07.150
[thrusters whooshing]

42:07.150 --> 42:13.531
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:13.531 --> 42:16.201
[computer blipping]

42:23.833 --> 42:30.840
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:40.725 --> 42:42.143
[laughs]

42:43.395 --> 42:45.438
Hey, guys, it's working.

42:45.438 --> 42:47.732
[laughs]

42:47.732 --> 42:48.775
[laughs softly]

42:48.775 --> 42:55.198
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:55.198 --> 42:58.410
<i>[Alex] Ladies and gentlemen,
we are climbing higher.</i>

42:58.410 --> 43:00.328
- We did it! We did it.
<i>- [Alex laughs]</i>

43:00.328 --> 43:03.373
- Hot dog!
- Whoo!

43:03.373 --> 43:05.375
[exhales heavily]

43:05.375 --> 43:11.172
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:17.721 --> 43:19.055
[Holden] Hey.

43:20.932 --> 43:22.934
Wei said you were
feeling better.

43:25.812 --> 43:28.481
When you see my blowtorch,
could you bring it back to me?

43:30.942 --> 43:32.485
[softly]
Eh, you can find it yourself.

43:33.653 --> 43:37.115
Dr. Okoye figured out
a treatment for your eyes.

43:38.325 --> 43:40.618
Really?

43:40.618 --> 43:42.996
We're getting out of here?

43:42.996 --> 43:44.205
She just tested it on herself

43:44.205 --> 43:46.249
and her eyesight's
already coming back.

43:46.249 --> 43:47.751
She's prepping
to treat everyone.

43:49.002 --> 43:50.879
How...

43:50.879 --> 43:53.089
I didn't think
you could pull it off.

43:53.089 --> 43:56.092
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

43:56.092 --> 43:57.385
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:57.385 --> 43:59.137
Now I can say
I took you in a fight.

44:00.513 --> 44:02.390
You can say whatever you want.

44:02.390 --> 44:07.562
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:07.562 --> 44:10.648
[Holden grunting]

44:12.192 --> 44:13.902
[door clangs]

44:13.902 --> 44:15.445
- [grunts]
- [door creaks]

44:16.946 --> 44:18.365
[door clangs and creaks]

44:19.866 --> 44:21.284
[shouts]

44:21.284 --> 44:23.161
- [panting]
- [air whooshing]

44:28.500 --> 44:31.503
[wind whooshing]

44:34.214 --> 44:37.217
[waves lapping]

44:43.515 --> 44:45.517
[device chirps]

44:50.230 --> 44:54.234
Holden, the tow is working.

44:54.234 --> 44:56.569
We're stabilizing
the <i>Barb's</i> orbit.

44:57.946 --> 45:00.156
Good news is now contagious.

45:01.324 --> 45:03.701
We figured out how to restore
everyone's vision.

45:04.661 --> 45:07.664
<i>My cancer meds
were why I was immune.</i>

45:08.540 --> 45:10.417
We're treating everyone now.

45:11.626 --> 45:14.838
Something good finally
came out of being on Eros.

45:17.298 --> 45:19.884
All we did was
buy ourselves more time.

45:19.884 --> 45:23.263
And that's what
we're going to keep on doing.

45:23.263 --> 45:26.266
<i>[hopeful music]</i>

45:26.266 --> 45:32.230
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:37.360 --> 45:39.571
Go ahead.
I want to be alone.

45:46.411 --> 45:49.414
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

45:49.414 --> 45:52.959
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:52.959 --> 45:55.253
Miss Gao, can we just have
a moment of your time, please?

45:55.253 --> 45:59.048
I just want to say that
it has been a very sad day,

45:59.048 --> 46:01.426
but our
Secretary-General's words

46:01.426 --> 46:03.094
to the families of the marines

46:03.094 --> 46:06.764
and her honesty for accepting
the blame for her missteps

46:06.764 --> 46:09.392
show why she is
such an honorable woman.

46:10.393 --> 46:11.853
Miss Gao,
do you have any comments

46:11.853 --> 46:13.396
on the new images
from New Terra?

46:13.396 --> 46:15.106
Do they change your position
on the Ring Gate

46:15.106 --> 46:16.941
and exploring new worlds?

46:18.943 --> 46:22.280
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:22.280 --> 46:24.449
<i>[woman] ...has been an
emotional day for the planet,</i>

46:24.449 --> 46:25.658
<i>to say the least.</i>

46:25.658 --> 46:27.494
<i>What began
as a day of mourning</i>

46:27.494 --> 46:29.704
<i>has now quickly evolved
to a watershed moment</i>

46:29.704 --> 46:32.081
<i>in our planet's history.</i>

46:32.081 --> 46:33.666
<i>We don't have
all the facts yet,</i>

46:33.666 --> 46:35.710
<i>but we do know that
opinions around the world</i>

46:35.710 --> 46:37.879
<i>dramatically changed
about the Ring Gate</i>

46:37.879 --> 46:41.007
<i>since these images
from New Terra became public.</i>

46:41.007 --> 46:43.760
<i>A UN spokesperson
has condemned the media</i>

46:43.760 --> 46:46.638
<i>for the irresponsible release
of classified information</i>

46:46.638 --> 46:49.432
<i>and said that an investigation
of the security breach</i>

46:49.432 --> 46:51.726
<i>is currently underway.</i>

46:57.148 --> 47:00.276
[door clicks open and shut]

47:00.276 --> 47:02.111
I said I want to be alone.

47:02.111 --> 47:04.322
Did you leak the images
from New Terra?

47:07.116 --> 47:08.743
- Yes.
[Arjun] You said the last thing

47:08.743 --> 47:11.287
you wanted to do was
unnecessarily scare the planet.

47:11.287 --> 47:14.332
I did, but now
it was necessary.

47:14.332 --> 47:15.625
Because you're scared to lose?

47:15.625 --> 47:17.585
I had to change the narrative.

47:17.585 --> 47:20.630
Now Nancy Gao doesn't have
a leg or a platform to stand on.

47:20.630 --> 47:22.674
You're inciting
fear and hysteria

47:22.674 --> 47:24.384
to cover up your own mistake.

47:24.384 --> 47:26.719
New Terra
is the headline again,

47:26.719 --> 47:29.097
as it always should have been.

47:29.097 --> 47:32.684
Nothing else in this election
ever should have mattered.

47:35.770 --> 47:37.355
This isn't about
the Ring worlds.

47:37.355 --> 47:38.940
It's about your pride.

47:38.940 --> 47:42.944
You told me to connect
with the voters emotionally.

47:42.944 --> 47:44.320
At the memorial,

47:44.320 --> 47:47.615
they saw me as the caring
matriarch you told me to be,

47:47.615 --> 47:50.285
and now they know
I was right to be cautious

47:50.285 --> 47:52.954
about exploring the new worlds.

47:52.954 --> 47:56.374
You wanted me
to play this game,

47:56.374 --> 47:58.001
so I did.

47:58.001 --> 47:59.794
You don't get
to be upset with me

47:59.794 --> 48:01.921
because I didn't play
by your rules.

48:01.921 --> 48:04.299
All your words today
were lies.

48:05.216 --> 48:07.385
There is nothing righteous
in winning this way.

48:07.385 --> 48:09.178
I did what needed to be done.

48:09.178 --> 48:12.599
You used our son's death
for political advantage!

48:12.599 --> 48:19.606
<i>♪ ♪</i>

48:19.606 --> 48:22.442
What I said about Charanpal,

48:22.442 --> 48:24.736
that wasn't a lie.

48:26.321 --> 48:28.239
Every word was the truth.

48:28.239 --> 48:35.246
<i>♪ ♪</i>

48:39.751 --> 48:40.960
[machine beeps]

48:43.004 --> 48:46.007
[indistinct chatter]

48:49.636 --> 48:51.054
[syringe whirs]

48:52.972 --> 48:59.979
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:01.314 --> 49:02.732
[man] This way.
This way.

49:07.320 --> 49:14.327
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:31.260 --> 49:33.805
- [device beeps]
- This is Murtry.

49:33.805 --> 49:35.264
Has the light shuttle
been prepared

49:35.264 --> 49:37.266
with the proximity detonator?

49:47.652 --> 49:50.655
<i>[eerie music]</i>

49:50.655 --> 49:55.618
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:55.618 --> 49:57.578
Miller.

49:57.578 --> 49:59.038
Where the hell have you been?

49:59.038 --> 50:01.791
<i>[ominous music]</i>

50:01.791 --> 50:04.293
<i>♪ ♪</i>

50:04.293 --> 50:07.338
- [blipping]
- [no audible dialogue]

50:07.338 --> 50:12.343
<i>♪ ♪</i>

50:13.386 --> 50:17.014
[visceral scream]
